Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of Artificial Intelligence (AI) in creating art, which falls under the category of cs.AI. It also discusses the history of technologies that automated aspects of art, such as photography and animation, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also touches on the human-computer interaction aspect of AI tools for art making, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses the philosophical question of whether computers can be credited with authorship of artwork, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
